# PDP Versions (v1 frozen, v2 pivot)

The PDP ships two versions on the same codebase:

- **v1** (`/v1`, legacy `/`) — frozen current design. The brand-team baseline.
- **v2** (`/v2`) — stakeholder pivot. All new pivot work goes here.

Full reference: `docs/pdp-versions.md`.

## Rules

- Read `docs/pdp-versions.md` before editing any PDP code.
- v2 changes go in `src/components/pdp/version/` or behind flags in `pdp-version-config.ts`. Never rewrite v1 defaults.
- Do not branch on `version === "v2"` across the codebase. Add a flag to `PdpVersionConfig` and read it.
- Never edit `pdp-data.ts` or `pdp-section-chapters.ts` for v2 needs. Those are the frozen v1 data.
- Never add v2-only CSS to `globals.css`. Put it in `src/app/v2/pdp-v2.css`, scoped under `[data-pdp-version="v2"]`.
- The shared design system (grid, typography, icons, motion tokens) stays shared — do not fork it per version.
- After any v2 change, confirm `/v1` still matches the baseline, then run `pnpm check:versions`.

## Quick map

- Provider/hook: `src/components/pdp/version/pdp-version-context.tsx` (`usePdpVersion()`)
- Config adapter: `src/components/pdp/version/pdp-version-config.ts` (`getPdpVersionConfig(version)`)
- v2 slides: `src/components/pdp/version/pdp-data-v2.ts`
- v2 chapters: `src/components/pdp/version/pdp-section-chapters-v2.ts`
- Boundary checks: `scripts/check-pdp-version-boundaries.mjs`
